<h1 id='contribute-to-documentation'>Contribute to Documentation</h1><h2 id='modules'>Modules</h2>
<p>All the modules are documented in separate markdown files in the modules directory.</p>
<h3 id='module-structure'>Module Structure</h3>
<p>The function module is written in markdown.<br>
It consists of a brief pseudo code and the fortran as well as the python code for that module</p>
<h2 id='tangling'>Tangling</h2>
<p><code>tangle.sh</code> is a bash script that builds a final index.html file which is then reflected in the documentation</p>

<aside class="success">
Remember â€” The sequence of files in `tangle.sh` matters
</aside>
<pre class="highlight shell"><code>rm ../index.html.md
cat Degrad.md &gt; ../index.html.md
cat Mixer.md &gt;&gt; ../index.html.md
cat Setup.md &gt;&gt; ../index.html.md
cat Density.md &gt;&gt; ../index.html.md
cat Tail.md &gt;&gt; ../index.html.md
</code></pre>
<aside class="warning">The directory structure is to be preserved for the framework to work properly. </aside>

<aside class="success">Build documentation using <code>sh tangle.sh</code></aside>
